{"title_page": "Ashika Ranganath", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Ashika Ranganath\n| sobriquet          = Karnataka Crush\n| image              = \n| caption            = \n| native_name        = \n| birth_name         = Ashika\n| birth_date         = <!--Birthdate must be attributed to a reliable published source with an established reputation for fact-checking. No blogs. No IMDb. No public records. See \nWP:BLPPRIVACY-->\n| death_date         = \n| death_place        = \n| residence          = [[Bangalore]], [[Karnataka]], India\n| nationality        = Indian\n| othername          = Karnataka Crush\n| occupation         = [[Actress]]\n| yearsactive        = 2016 - Present\n| spouse             = \n| children           = \n}}\n'''Ashika Ranganath''' is an Indian actress. She rose to fame via the 2016 film, [[Crazy Boy (film)|''Crazy Boy'']]<ref>{{cite news |title= Ashikakiran joins Garuda camp! |url= http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/hindi/2017/may/06/ashika-joins-garuda-camp-1601543.html|newspaper= [[The Indian Express]]}}</ref> as female lead.. She later starred in ''[[Mass Leader]]'' and ''[[Mugulu Nage]]''.<ref>{{cite news |title= Ashika Ranganath joins Raju Kannada Medium |url= http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movies/Ashika-Ranganath-joins-raju-kannada-medium/articleshow/56513434.cms|newspaper= [[The Times of India]]}}</ref> \n\n== Early life ==\n\nRanganath was brought up by her father N. Ranganath, a Civil Contractor, and mother, B. Sudha Ranganath, a housewife.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/kannada/2017/jan/18/team-mugulu-nage--shoots-at-scenic-puducherry-1561019.html|title=Team Mugulu Nage shoots at scenic Puducherry|newspaper=[[The Indian Express]]}}</ref> Ranganath's elder sister Anusha Ranganath is also an actress.\n\nRanganath studied in Bishop Sargant School, [[Tumkur]] and later moved to [[Bangalore]], the capital of [[Karnataka]], for pre-in [[Jyoti Nivas College, Bangalore|Jyoti Nivas College]], where she auditioned for a Clean and Clear Fresh Face Bangalore contest, emerging as the runner-up of Miss Fresh Face 2014.\n\nRanganath was trained in various dance forms including freestyle, Bollywood, Belly and western.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/kannada/2017/apr/04/russian-model-debuts-in-gurunandan-starrer-raju-kannada-medium-1589886.html|title=Russian model debuts in Gurunandan-starrer Raju Kannada medium|newspaper=[[The Indian Express]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/kannada/2017/apr/04/ganesh-on-shooting-spree-no-time-to-chill-1589885.html|title=Ganesh on shooting spree, no time to chill|newspaper=[[The Indian Express]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.prajavani.net/news/article/2017/05/26/494097.html|title=\u0ca4\u0cc1\u0c82\u0c9f \u0cb0\u0cb5\u0cbf \u0cb8\u0ccd\u0cb5\u0c82\u0ca4 \u0c95\u0ca8\u0cb8\u0cc1\u0c97\u0cb3\u0cc1|publisher=[[Prajavani]]}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\n\nHer career in acting started after ''Crazy Boy'' director Mahesh Babu picked her during a Clean and Clear Fresh Face Bangalore contest. She was nominated for the [[South Indian International Movie Awards|Best Debutant Actress in a Leading Role Award by SIIMA]].<ref>{{cite news |title= Leader challenges brutal cold|url= http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/kannada/2017/jan/30/leader-challenges-brutal-cold-1564935.html|newspaper= [[The Indian Express]]}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n<br />\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!No\n!Year\n! Film\n! Role\n!Director\n! Notes\n|-\n|1\n|2016\n|''[[Crazy Boy (film)|Crazy Boy]]''|| Nandini\n|Mahesh Babu|| Nominated- [[SIIMA Award for Best Debutant Actor - Kannada|SIIMA Award for Best Debutant Actor in a Leading Role (Female)- Kannada]]\n|-\n|2\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2017\n|''[[Mass Leader]]''|| Shreya\n|narasimha||\n|-\n|3\n|''[[Mugulu Nage]]''|